      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Karahanaenone, a terpenoid isolated from oil of hops, has been synthesized by the thermal reaction shown. Identify the kind of pericyclic reaction, and explain how karahanaenone is formed.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ3dhIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--613567a154d3ca9555db4cc223e603342ce6865f/OChem_30_EC_020.jpg\" alt=\"Cyclopentane having oxygen atom, methyl, methine double bonded to methylene, and double bond linked to two methyl groups reacts with heat to form Karahanaenone with double bond at C 4.\">",
